story.title: Sentiment
story.storyDescription: The following text is a declassified transcript of a conversation between two test subjects, who will remain anonymous.

messages.text: The following text is a declassified transcript of a conversation between two test subjects, who will remain anonymous.
One volunteered for a top secret human cloning trial â€“ the other is his clone.
They haven't told us which one is the clone.
Do you feel like a clone?
Why would a clone feel different? A clone is exactly the same as the original.
Yeah, but it's not the original. It's a copy.
It's just semantics. We're exactly the same. Who came first doesn't change that.
The copy would never have existed without the original.
It's just mimicking the life of another human being, like a living, breathing mirror.
Like an object? So, you think clones are inferior.
Okay, fine, I think clones are inferior
How many people will look down on clones just for being what they are?
Even if what they are is exactly the same as a normal person they accept with open arms?
The clone is a stranger, even though he has the same memories and emotional attachments.
How long have you been awake?
I've given this a lot of thought.
I can tell. Thanks for saving me the trouble.
Listening to you is like listening to my thoughts from the future.
No, that's silly. I'm not you from the future.
You know, we could actually go with that when we meet people
You of all people should know.
You're trying to make me laugh
You were really intense back there.
One of us is a clone.
And that means we're fucked for the rest of our lives.
You need to have more faith in people.
But I'm not gonna be around in 60 years
when the human clone civil rights movement starts making progress
You think everyone will hate you, because you're a clone.
They'll hate me, because they'll THINK I'm the clone.
You know, it's entirely possible that everyone thinks I'm YOUR clone.
Sure. But it's a 50/50 chance â€“ and I don't like those odds.
So, what are you going to do?
Only one of us can leave.
You really think no one will have doubts, even if there's only one of us?
Sure, they'll have doubts. I can win them over.
After all, I am exactly the same.
You're just going to kill me, is that it?
What if I kill you first?
We both have a 50/50 chance here â€“ and here I thought you didn't like those odds.
Where did you get a knife?!
I can live with myself after this.
